      'Far in the north, surrounded by snow-capped mountains, lay the Kingdom of Frost Crystal. Five-year-old Princess Elsa had silver hair, eyes the color of sapphires, and a secret that both thrilled and terrified her — her hands could create ice and snow.',
      'Three days ago, she had accidentally frozen the garden fountain when she felt excited. Last night, a nightmare woke her and turned her whole bedroom into an ice cave. Today was her birthday, and she made one silent wish to the sky: "Please, please don\'t let anything go wrong."',
